      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my tomato plants are acting weird. the leaves on the bottom are turning all yellow and kind of pale. any idea what happened or how to fix it?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yellowing leaves, especially on the lower half of a tomato plant, can be a common issue. It's likely due to inadequate light, which can cause the plant to produce less chlorophyll and more ethylene, leading to a yellowing effect. You can try moving the plant to a brighter location or supplementing with grow lights. Additionally, ensure the soil is consistently moist but not waterlogged, as this can also contribute to the issue.",
